✅ Time Complexity of Arrays.sort() in Java:
For int[] (primitive types):
Java uses a Dual-Pivot QuickSort algorithm.

Average Case: O(n log n)

Worst Case: O(n²) (rare due to optimizations)

Best Case: O(n log n)

✅ So the time complexity for Arrays.sort(int[]) is typically:

java
Copy
Edit
O(n log n)
⚠️ Note:
For primitive arrays (int[], double[], etc.), it uses Dual-Pivot QuickSort.

For objects (Integer[], String[], etc.), it uses TimSort (a hybrid of MergeSort and InsertionSort):

Best: O(n)

Average/Worst: O(n log n)

